snippet.textDisplay:
When I used to smoke, I ran a small janitorial service. One night I washed the walls of an office where a chain-smoker worked. In my ignorance at the time, I didn't wear any type of gloves. I decided to take a break after cleaning half the office and went to the lobby to smoke a cigarette. I had to quickly find a place to sit because I suddenly got lightheaded and couldn't stand without holding onto something like the receptionists counter.

My point of telling this story is to remind anyone who works with chemicals to please remember your gloves. Your skin will absorb nicotine suspended in water and will get in your bloodstream...quickly. The part of the video where he was cleaning the floor mats without gloves made me think of this.
